node.text: We closed on our new house today! 🎉I can’t believe it! What a whirlwind the last two months have been! I wanted to give you a full home tour of the empty house before we move in this weekend Stay tuned until the very end...that’s when I share the big project we have planned for the house and one of the main reasons why we decided to move! We can’t wait to move in, get settled, and begin sharing this new adventure with all of you! ❤️🏡

node.text:
Today I’m sharing a walk through of my entire house (every single room!), which I’ve actually never done before on my page! I’m sharing rooms I’ve never shown before including my laundry room and mud room! 

If you missed it, we are selling our house! Get all the info on our move on my website, Mytexashouse.com. All sources are linked on the LIKEtoKNOW.it app or by clicking the link in my IG bio!

*update: House sold. We moved! 

#hometour #realestate #houseforsale #mytexashouse #texashomes #texasrealestate #falldecor #homedecor

node.title: We’re Selling Our House!: A Complete Home Tour of “Mytexashouse”!

node.text: Here’s my super easy way to put on a duvet cover! No more actually climbing inside of the duvet to install it! 🙈😂 The first step, which isn’t shown, is to turn the duvet cover INSIDE OUT! Then lay the duvet insert over the cover and tie all four sides of the duvet to the insert! Roll them like a burrito. Turn back out the ends like a sandwich baggie, and then voila!✨...the duvet cover is perfectly placed on the duvet in under 2 minutes!🙌🏻 And you can do this technique on your bed instead of the floor if you want. 😉 Link to products/outfit: http://liketk.it/2LMSl

node.title: How to put on a duvet cover in under 2 minutes!

node.text: This is a beautiful home we toured today by Darling Homes in the Montgomery Farms neighborhood in Allen, TX. This is a 4 bedroom home (option for 5th bedroom) with about 5,000 square feet of living space. My favorite part of the home was the large open living room and kitchen space with all the floor to ceiling windows overlooking the patio! I also LOVE that there was a huge pantry and even a prep kitchen! Check out the IGTV video for the full tour of this beautiful home! What is your favorite part of this home?!!

node.title: Model Home Tour: Darling Homes, Allen, TX (priced from: $900K+)

This model home is in Arlington, Texas (right near Dallas. TX). This is a Toll Brothers Home in the Viridian master planned community. The model is called the “Valen”. I recently toured this beautiful modern farmhouse style home in Parker, Texas in the Whitestone Estates neighborhood. It is a one story home, on a one acre lot and has a 3 car garage, 4 bedrooms and is approx 4500 square feet. A spec home in this neighborhood, similar to the model, is selling for $823K.
Mytexashouse.com

node.text:
Took some pics of Jessie today in our bathroom and they turned out like a sultry boudoir photo shoot!😂🐶 We feel like she’s acting perkier since she started her new heart medication! 🙏🏻 Hope she gets back to her sassy self soon! ❤️

And I’m excited to let you guys know that this rug, which we’ve named the “Austin” is officially one of the new rug designs that will be launching next month at Walmart! 🎉 It will come in 3 different colorways as well!! This one…which has ivory, golds, blues. A “blue”one which has a gorgeous all over blue color, and a “neutral” version which will be an all over ivory/beige color! I’m obsessed with the vintage look of the Austin and excited to be adding some fun colors to my rug collection! 💙💛🧡

I’ve linked my bathroom sources (except the rug which will be available mid October!) on the LTK app. Just search “mytexashouse” to find my shop on the app! Or click the link in my Instagram bio! http://liketk.it/3nRuo

Hey guys! Ok, I need your opinions! Which one of my new @walmart outfits should wear in my pics for my new Walmart Fall/Winter home decor collection photo shoot? #ad The pics will be up on Walmart.com 😬, so I’m having a hard time picking… should I go casual? Dressy? Professional? And should I wear my hair up or hair down?👱🏻‍♀️👩🏼 And don’t worry, I won’t wear the purse in the photo shoot! Lol! 

So many cute things from Walmart to chose from this season! I’m obsessed with this flirty shirt dress (which I got in a couple colors) and you can’t ever go wrong with a classy blazer and black jeans! I just got a new blog post up on all the info on my new fall outfits from Walmart including links and size information! Now if it would only cool down here so it actually feels like fall! 🍂🍁🍂

And all outfits are also linked in my stories today and on my shop in the @shop.ltk app! @walmartfashion #walmartfashion #liketkit http://liketk.it/3nMUj

node.text:
Hey guys! Thanks so much for your kind words regarding Jessie and her health diagnosis I shared yesterday in my stories. As we feared, she is in the very early stages of congestive heart failure. 😞 According to our vet, unfortunately heart issues like this plague her breed and can often happen at a relatively young age (before the age of 10, like Jessie). Though we are really hopeful with the help of medication that she will start to feel better and it will allow us to have a lot more time with her!🙏🏻❤️ I so appreciate all the love and prayers sent our way! Jessie is truly one-of-a-kind and honestly I can’t imagine life without her!🐶💕

I’m writing this in the parking lot of Starbucks because our internet is down in our area and our house gets terrible cell service! 🙈 Our internet company says it could take awhile to get service up again….sooo if you don’t hear from me for a few days this is why! 😫🤦‍♀️ Lol!

My kitchen sources are linked on my shop on the LTK app as well as on my website (link in bio). http://liketk.it/3nIDs

Hey guys! Today in my stories I’m sharing this year’s fall dining room decor! I went for warm fall palette of muted rust and orange! 🍁🍂And restocked alert!! 🚨 I wanted to let you know that my farmhouse style extension dining table is finally back in stock! 

Also, in my stories I’m sharing a little update on Jessie’s health. I mentioned yesterday that we needed to get her checked out at the vet due to some concerning symptoms. Well, we got some news today which I talk about in my stories. ❤️🐶❤️

node.text:
I’m often asked how I’m able to have white furniture with kids and pets. We have had this tufted sofa for over 7 years and it still looks brand new! The reason? The sofa is made of performance (polypropylene) fabric, which is the same stain resistant fiber used in the My Texas House rugs as well as in upholstered outdoor furniture! The sofa cushion covers can be washed in the washing machine or even bleached! Thank goodness for washable/stain resistant cushion covers because as you can see my family doesn’t go easy on our sofa! 🙈🥴 

The weirdest thing I found this time under the sofa cushions??….6 popsicle sticks, and a gold necklace! No money though! 😏🤷‍♀️😂 What’s the weirdest thing you’ve found under your cushions? 

All sources are linked in my shop on the LTK app! 👉 http://liketk.it/3nzmd  The sofa is from Restoration Hardware, but an identical one is linked from Pottery Barn and can be ordered with performance fabric. We also have the affordable Wayfair version (not performance fabric) in our media room.

node.text:
Hey guys! Did you catch my stories yesterday? I shared all the details of my new fall mantel look! It appears my new fall garland I linked already sold out in this longer 9 foot length (I’m sure they’ll eventually restock), but I also linked the two shorter lengths. Or if you really like the 9 foot length (and need it now!) they have some neutral color versions that you could add a few colorful fall stems to! Either way, this was an easy to install on my mantel using my favorite holiday decor must-haves….Command Strip Hooks!! Have you decorated for fall yet or do you prefer a Halloween look? Or perhaps you just wait to decorate for the holidays until Christmas?! 

Follow me on the @shop.LTK app to shop this post and get my exclusive app-only content! #liketkit #LTKhome #LTKSeasonal @shop.ltk http://liketk.it/3nnzT

Ok, so I experimented and made this video specifically for my TiKTok page using one of their trending songs!  I wasn’t going to share it on here, but I had so many people on my TikTok page saying they had one of my rugs but didn’t know anything about them…so I thought these cleaning tips would be helpful for all my Insta friends too (this is the “extended version” of the original TikTok video!). Jessie’s reaction “😳” is my favorite, so I slowed it down for all to enjoy!😂

For more info about my rug collection head to mytexashouse.com where I just got a new blog post up with cleaning info and links! http://liketk.it/3ncY0

Hey! Hope you had a great long weekend! I’ve been starting to photograph all my new collection coming to Walmart.com soon (still waiting on my rug samples though!). node.text:
Did a little thing today on our front porch! I mean what else would I do when it’s 104 degrees outside?! 🥵🍁🤗 September means it’s fall decor time! 

My little garland hack is super easy…just use a hot glue gun (ours is a construction grade one from Home Depot) and glue on command strip hooks all around the door! I attached the hooks directly to the brick. My wreaths are attached with command strip hooks as well! 

Now I just need to get to a pumpkin patch to add some real pumpkins. And also, very important question, has anyone seen if Costco has their huge mum plants out this year year?!!!

All sources (or similar) are linked here👉 http://liketk.it/3n32o

node.text:
Here is my quick fall floral arrangement tutorial! 🌸🌸🌸 Complete bouquet “recipe” below! 👇👇👇

1) Start by creating a supportive grid with tape (scotch tape works great!)
2) Place largest flowers first
3) Work in a triangle formation and then fill in gaps with smaller flowers
4) Use longer draping stems (like the lilacs and eucalyptus here) near the bottom of arrangement to give it a flowy & whimsical look

🌸 My Fall Bouquet “Recipe”🌸
2 mauve hydrangea
3 ivory hydrangea 
1 white marigold bundle 
5 pink dahlia stems (2 large, 3 small)
2 lilac stems 
2 rose stems 
3 peony stems 
2 large rust colored rose bundles 
2 pink seeded stems for texture 
2 eucalyptus stems to add a touch of green 

I linked all flowers (or similar) on the LTK app! 👉http://liketk.it/3mUEJ

Can you believe it’s almost September?😱 Where did the summer go?! But now that September is here, it’s a bit more socially acceptable to have up Fall decor (lol! Not that it stopped me😂). So I went full Fall with my bedroom decor today! 🍁🍂🍁

Do you recognize this buffalo check quilt set? It’s actually the reverse side of the Primrose bedding set from my Walmart collection! I thought it would be perfect to use for Fall! It’s available now and linked on this post in the LTK app! 

And you’re also getting your first sneak peek at one of the new bedding sets that I’ll be launching soon at Walmart! 🤗🎉 This bed in a bag comforter set has cute little ties on the ends and button detailing across the middle! The set also will come with matching shams with ties, a complete sheet set and a set of three euro size decorative pillows (not shown)!! I’ll be sharing the whole set soon (it will come in several different colors). 

Finally, the Dahlia rug from my collection is on sale right now at Walmart!! The 8x10 size seen here is only $170!!! Amazing price for this beautiful rug!😱
http://liketk.it/3mQEV #falldecor #homedecor #bedroom #beddingsets #bedroomdecor #fall
